==Translingual==

===Letter===
'''Đ''' '''đ'''

#The fifth letter of the [[Vietnamese]] alphabet (seventh, counting [[Â]] and [[Ê]]), [[Quốc ngữ]], preceded by [[D]] and followed by [[E]], and representing /d/.
#The 8th letter of the [[Bosnian]] alphabet, sometimes spelled as '''dj''', preceded by [[Dž]] and followed by [[E]], and representing /dʑ/. [[Đ]] and [[Dž]] are quite often confused by non-native speakers.
#The 8th letter of the [[Croatian]] alphabet, sometimes spelled as '''dj''', preceded by [[Dž]] and followed by [[E]], and representing /dʑ/. [[Đ]] and [[Dž]] are quite often confused by non-native speakers.
#The 8th letter of the [[Serbian]] Roman alphabet, sometimes written as '''dj''', preceded by [[Dž]] and followed by [[E]], and representing /dʑ/. Its Cyrillic counterpart is [[Ђ]]. [[Đ]] and [[Dž]] are quite often confused by non-native speakers.
#The 7th letter of the [[North Sámi]] alphabet, preceded by [[D]] and followed by [[E]], and representing /ð/.
#A letter in the [[Old English]] alphabet (''eth'') representing "th" as in "this".

===Technical note===
The Vietnamese letter, represented in Unicode as U+0110, is not the same as the North Sámi character.

